title: The Adventures of a Dog, and a Good Dog Too
creator: Alfred Elwes
description: LibriVox recording of The Adventures of a Dog, and a Good Dog Too, by Alfred Elwes. Read by Allyson Hester. This fictional work is written in 1st person by the dog himself. It's a cute story of the adventures in the life of a noble dog who is appropriately named, Job. The canine society in which he lives is an interesting parallel to human society. (Summary by Allyson Hester) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (65MB)
subject: librivox; literature; audiobook; adventure; animals; children; fantasy; fiction
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
